<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-08-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="270" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d270">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Neill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                        States Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lima,
                                    Peru</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-29"><hi rend="italic">August 29, 1895</hi></date>.
                                (Received September 24.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 237.]</seg></opener>
                        <p>Sir: Referring to the claim of the Hydrographic Commission of the Amazon,
                            I have the honor to report that as the ordinary session of <pb facs="0320" n="1054" xml:id="pg_1054"/> Congress opens to-morrow, I
                            have this day placed a note in the hands of his excellency Senor Manuel
                            Candamo, minister for foreign relations of Peru, regarding this
                            long-pending claim of citizens of the United States upon the Peruvian
                            Government, and respectfully asking his excellency to have the claim
                            presented to this Congress for its early consideration, as per my
                            inclosed note.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard R. Neill.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 237.]</seg></opener>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Neill</persName> to
                                    Señor <persName type="to">Candamo</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-29"><hi rend="italic">August 29,
                                        1895</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 56.]</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Minister</hi>: I would again respectfully
                                call the attention of your excellency to the many notes from this
                                legation regarding the payment of the long-pending claim of citizens
                                of the United States upon the Government of Peru known as the
                                Hydrographic Commission of the Amazon, and in view of the opening
                                to-morrow (the 30th instant) of the ordinary session of Congress, I
                                would respectfully ask if your excellency will have the claim
                                presented to this Congress for its early consideration.</p>
                            <p>I avail myself, etc.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard R. Neill.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>